value.title: White House lifts Trump order that temporarily banned certain immigrant visas during pandemic
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden on Wednesday revoked a Trump-era executive order that temporarily banned some immigrant visas during the coronavirus pandemic

value.title: Trump aide, 27, launches GOP primary bid against Kinzinger, blasts 'Fake Republican' incumbent
value.excerpt: Just weeks after voting in support of the second impeachment of former President Donald Trump, U.S. Rep. Adam Kinzinger, R-Ill., is already facing a pro-Trump GOP primary challenger.

value.title: Hannity reacts to Dems' letter pressuring Biden to give up nuclear authority: 'Must be totally humiliating'
value.excerpt: Fox News host Sean Hannity reacted Wednesday night to the reports suggesting House Democrats were urging President Biden to relinquish his nuclear authority.

value.title: Louisiana GOP Rep. Higgins challenges Biden 'to live without oil & gas'
value.excerpt: Louisiana Republican Rep. Clay Higgins floated an environmental challenge to President Biden Tuesday – introducing a House resolution calling on the commander-in-chief to live without any petroleum products.

value.title: West Virginia gov urges Republicans to 'swallow' unrelated spending in Biden COVID-19 relief plan
value.excerpt: Republican West Virginia Gov. Jim Justice urged Senate Republicans Wednesday to "swallow" the hefty price tag of President Biden’s $1.9 trillion COVID-19 relief plan, warning lawmakers that "you will leave a lot of people hurting" if they continue to oppose the legislation.

value.title: Biden nominates three to USPS board of governors as DeJoy testifies on mail crises
value.excerpt: The White House moves to reassert control of the U.S. Postal Service as the postmaster general brushes off lawmakers’ calls to resign.

value.title: Biden says he will push for funding for semiconductor legislation
value.excerpt: U.S. President Joe Biden said on Wednesday he will push for funding for semiconductor legislation following a meeting with bipartisan group of lawmakers about supply chain issues.

value.title: Donald Trump Jr. deposed by DC attorney general as part of inaugural funds lawsuit
value.excerpt: Donald Trump Jr. was deposed as part of the Washington, DC, attorney general's lawsuit alleging the misuse of Trump inaugural funds, according to a new court filing.

value.title: Nikki Haley slams Biden push for seat on ‘sham’ Human Rights Council with ‘tyrants,' 'dictators’
value.excerpt: Former U.N. Ambassador Nikki Haley on Wednesday slammed the Biden administration’s move to reclaim a seat on the controversial Human Rights Council – noting that the Geneva-based body’s table includes human rights abusers.

value.title: Georgia counties seek legal fees for 'frivolous' Trump voter-fraud lawsuit

value.title: McCarthy and Cheney at odds over Trump's future role in the party
value.excerpt: House Minority Leader Kevin McCarthy (R-Calif) and Rep. Liz Cheney (R-Wyo.) disagreed Feb. 24 on former president Donald Trump's role in the Republican party.

value.title: Pence Reportedly Not Holding a Grudge Against Trump Over Whole Riot Thing
value.excerpt: It took a few weeks, but Pence seems to be over it — at least publicly. CNN reports that Pence told a group of Republican lawmakers on Tuesday that not only does he remain close friends with Trump, but that he has plans to launch a political action organization defending the administration’s record.

value.title: Biden’s 100-day deportation moratorium indefinitely banned by judge
value.excerpt: The Biden administration’s efforts to impose a 100-day pause on deportations were dealt another blow on Tuesday when a district judge extended a ban on its imposition in response to a lawsuit from Texas.

value.title: Romney says Trump would win 2024 GOP nomination "in a landslide" if he ran for president

value.title: Trump stacked his Cabinet with climate skeptics. Now Republicans are piling on Biden's climate activist nominee
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden nominated the most diverse Cabinet in history, but the Senate, which gets to offer "advice and consent," is suddenly full of members -- mostly Republicans -- who are critical of partisan tweets and are carefully scrutinizing nominees' job qualifications.

value.title: Biden's Covid plan gets backing from more than 150 top business leaders
value.excerpt: More than 150 senior executives from some of the largest American companies across several major industries have lined up behind President Joe Biden's $1.9 trillion coronavirus relief package, according to a letter obtained by CNN.

value.title: Major Trump backer Rebekah Mercer orchestrates Parler’s second act
value.excerpt: Rebekah Mercer, a daughter of a major Republican donor, is a founding investor of Parler, where she reportedly is pulling strings. Mercer holds the majority stake in Parler and controlled two of three board seats as of early February — a board to which she recently appointed allies.

value.title: Critics slam Sen. Ron Johnson for unfounded claim that ‘fake Trump protesters’ led riots: ‘It’s disgraceful’
value.excerpt: Sen. Ron Johnson (R-Wis.) made false claims minimizing the damage done by a pro-Trump mob during the Jan. 6 Capitol riot.

value.title: LIVE UPDATES: Joe Biden has yet to declare Uighur abuses genocide
value.excerpt: Biden, who vowed to be tough on China while on the campaign trail, has been careful not to classify the human rights abuses against the Uighurs since entering office.

value.title: Trump should focus on 2022 elections, not 2024, in CPAC address: Newt Gingrich
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump should focus on next year's midterm elections when he addresses the Conservative Political Action Conference (CPAC) this weekend, former House Speaker Newt Gingrich told "Hannity."

value.title: Romney says Trump likely Republican nominee if he runs in 2024
value.excerpt: Sen. Mitt Romney reportedly said Tuesday if former President Trump were to run again he would likely win the Republican nomination for president.

value.title: AOC tears into Biden admin for reopening child migrant facility: 'This is not okay'
value.excerpt: Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez, D-N.Y., had some strong words for President Biden's administration after news surfaced that it was reopening a child migrant detention facility in Texas.

value.title: Biden says US, Canada 'doubled down' on efforts to fight climate change
value.excerpt: President Biden hosted his first bilateral meeting with Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau, where the pair pledged to strengthen their partnership and to address the COVID-19 pandemic, climate change and a middle-class economic recovery as a team.

value.title: Biden transition received donations from George Soros, Hollywood celebrities
value.excerpt: President Biden’s transition team raised more than $20 million, including contributions from renowned business moguls and staples in the Hollywood celebrity circuit.
